Dear Scratch Team,

I have been disappointed with the way that you have moderated Scratch Auth.

Scratch Auth is a utility that allows other websites to allow their users to log in with their Scratch account.

[big]Auth Project Removals[/big]

The Scratch Team has taken down Scratch Auth’s default authentication project multiple times.

The first auth project was at the code 676911023. It seems like it was removed on 2022 June 3rd.

All details on this initial deletion were shared on a forum topic titled [url=https://scratch.mit.edu/discuss/topic/609816/]Scratch Auth and Itinerary are censored[/url].

Here is the message that Looky received explaining the removal of the authentication project:

[quote=Message from Scratch Team]
Please do not share external links to inappropriate sites, link shorteners, browser extensions, or userscripts on Scratch. These are a safety concern, as they can hide malicious content. You can share a full link as long as it does not lead to inappropriate material, including sites that reveal personal information or social media accounts, or or have unmoderated chat features. [url=https://scratch.mit.edu/discuss/topic/284272/]Our policy[/url] on browser extensions and user scripts has more information. Thanks! - Scratch Team
[/quote]

It seems the issue with the Scratch Auth questionnaire that was going on at the time of removal. Scratch does not allow links to Google Forms, and the questionnaire was done through there. But in that case: why remove the entire project? Why not edit the form link out?

