This seems to me like 1 of 4 things:

[list=1]
[*] The Scratch Auth project was mass-reported by spam or troll accounts
[*] The Scratch Team needed at least [i]a[/i] reason to remove the project, even if that reason was completely wrong
[*] A Scratch Team member saw that a popular Scratch mod with less restrictive rules(that isn’t allowed to be linked) used Scratch Auth and saw that Scratch Auth had a project on Scratch, so took it down due to the Scratch mod, likely assuming that Scratch Auth was only made for that mod, and only used by this mod
[*] Links are not reviewed, and if a moderator does not recognize a link: they take down the project without reviewing the link(I’ve heard this as a reason before). (Context: the Scratch Auth project had a link to Scratch Auth in its title, and I assume Instructions and/or N&C)
